WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.928 align:middle line:90%


00:00:03.928 --> 00:00:07.856 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:07.856 --> 00:00:13.770 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.770 --> 00:00:18.180 align:middle line:84%
NARRATOR: I bow to the
mothers of Bhakti, the saints

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:23.550 align:middle line:84%
of mystic yoga, who blew
the seeds of divine love

00:00:23.550 --> 00:00:28.710 align:middle line:84%
into the hearts of women
all over the world.

00:00:28.710 --> 00:00:33.530 align:middle line:84%
I bow to those saints who
struggled and sacrificed

00:00:33.530 --> 00:00:39.260 align:middle line:84%
and paved the way for all
women to attain pure devotion.

00:00:39.260 --> 00:00:42.110 align:middle line:84%
Many of them will
never be known.

00:00:42.110 --> 00:00:47.540 align:middle line:84%
This is a tribute to them,
the unsung heroines of Bhakti.

00:00:47.540 --> 00:00:51.524 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:51.524 --> 00:02:13.260 align:middle line:90%


00:02:13.260 --> 00:02:16.050 align:middle line:84%
We are here to serve
and uplift the world.

00:02:16.050 --> 00:02:19.690 align:middle line:90%


00:02:19.690 --> 00:02:23.630 align:middle line:84%
A heart filled with love,
connected with the divine

00:02:23.630 --> 00:02:24.860 align:middle line:90%
can reach out to everyone.

00:02:24.860 --> 00:02:28.760 align:middle line:90%


00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:30.910 align:middle line:84%
Divine love is
the greatest love.

00:02:30.910 --> 00:02:35.380 align:middle line:90%


00:02:35.380 --> 00:02:40.960 align:middle line:84%
The saints of mystic yoga speak
of a beloved deep within souls.

00:02:40.960 --> 00:02:44.690 align:middle line:90%


00:02:44.690 --> 00:02:47.890 align:middle line:84%
I want to reawaken
that relationship.

00:02:47.890 --> 00:02:50.400 align:middle line:84%
Then Bhakti can flow
through my heart.

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:54.064 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:54.064 --> 00:03:35.390 align:middle line:90%


00:03:35.390 --> 00:03:42.090 align:middle line:10%
Bhakti is really an inherit
response of being alive,

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:46.750 align:middle line:10%
that is a natural flow, that
we can cultivate no matter

00:03:46.750 --> 00:03:48.760 align:middle line:10%
what background we're
from, no matter what

00:03:48.760 --> 00:03:50.730 align:middle line:10%
our spiritual orientation is.

00:03:50.730 --> 00:03:55.000 align:middle line:10%
We feel that connection,
that union with ourselves,

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:56.970 align:middle line:10%
with a divine
presence, with others.

00:03:56.970 --> 00:04:00.390 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't need to be
an Eastern practice.

00:04:00.390 --> 00:04:03.890 align:middle line:84%
Practice of Bhakti is the
practice of unconditional love.

00:04:03.890 --> 00:04:08.030 align:middle line:10%
It allows you to realize that
there's beauty and there's joy

00:04:08.030 --> 00:04:10.530 align:middle line:10%
and there's divinity
in everything

00:04:10.530 --> 00:04:11.800 align:middle line:10%
if you just look for it.

00:04:11.800 --> 00:04:14.960 align:middle line:10%
For me, Bhakti is the
heart, the core, of who

00:04:14.960 --> 00:04:17.670 align:middle line:10%
we are as people, as beings.

00:04:17.670 --> 00:04:21.690 align:middle line:84%
There's a piece of
divine in all us.

00:04:21.690 --> 00:04:23.540 align:middle line:90%
And we just need to uncover it.

00:04:23.540 --> 00:04:24.680 align:middle line:90%
We just need to remember it.

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:27.110 align:middle line:84%
Once you get on the path,
once you start to realize

00:04:27.110 --> 00:04:30.260 align:middle line:84%
that everything is
centered around a divinity,

00:04:30.260 --> 00:04:33.560 align:middle line:84%
you can't run anywhere
except into divinity.

00:04:33.560 --> 00:04:37.410 align:middle line:84%
You can run your eyes closed and
you'll never run off the path.

00:04:37.410 --> 00:04:39.820 align:middle line:10%
Bhakti is energy.

00:04:39.820 --> 00:04:41.135 align:middle line:10%
It's the energy of love.

00:04:41.135 --> 00:04:43.806 align:middle line:10%
And love has its source in God.

00:04:43.806 --> 00:04:44.780 align:middle line:90%
God is love.

00:04:44.780 --> 00:04:45.600 align:middle line:90%
Love is God.

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:49.130 align:middle line:84%
You're tapping in to
the greatest reservoir

00:04:49.130 --> 00:04:51.490 align:middle line:90%
of energy, which is love.

00:04:51.490 --> 00:04:54.910 align:middle line:10%
So with every person,
whether they're rich or poor,

00:04:54.910 --> 00:04:57.540 align:middle line:10%
whatever color,
nationality they are,

00:04:57.540 --> 00:05:02.040 align:middle line:10%
I strive to remember that
they want to be loved.

00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:05.090 align:middle line:10%
SHARON GANNON: You
enter into a mood

00:05:05.090 --> 00:05:08.010 align:middle line:10%
of receptivity, of surrender.

00:05:08.010 --> 00:05:13.795 align:middle line:10%
And you listen for what God
might want to say to you.

00:05:13.795 --> 00:05:16.290 align:middle line:10%
You listen for a
message from God.

00:05:16.290 --> 00:05:20.300 align:middle line:10%
To be a woman of Bhakti,
a woman of devotion,

00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:22.575 align:middle line:10%
doesn't mean that
you're perfect.

00:05:22.575 --> 00:05:29.750 align:middle line:84%
But you are in a dialogue,
in a heartfelt dialogue.

00:05:29.750 --> 00:05:33.450 align:middle line:84%
Unless you understand
a woman's nature,

00:05:33.450 --> 00:05:35.430 align:middle line:84%
you can't really
understand Bhakti.

00:05:35.430 --> 00:05:37.960 align:middle line:10%
But it's a female principle.

00:05:37.960 --> 00:05:40.390 align:middle line:10%
And the female principle is
that nourishing principle,

00:05:40.390 --> 00:05:44.260 align:middle line:10%
that giving principal,
that affection principle.

00:05:44.260 --> 00:05:46.520 align:middle line:84%
And that is, in the first
stage of every human

00:05:46.520 --> 00:05:47.760 align:middle line:90%
being is the mother.

00:05:47.760 --> 00:05:50.770 align:middle line:10%
For those people that grow
up in the Bhakti tradition,

00:05:50.770 --> 00:05:54.230 align:middle line:10%
the mother is probably one
of the most important people.

00:05:54.230 --> 00:05:58.840 align:middle line:84%
I mean, any good quality that
I have, it came from my mom.

00:05:58.840 --> 00:06:00.940 align:middle line:10%
And so from the time that
we wake up in the morning,

00:06:00.940 --> 00:06:03.840 align:middle line:10%
my mom would wake us
up and you meditate.

00:06:03.840 --> 00:06:05.340 align:middle line:90%
And that's start your day.

00:06:05.340 --> 00:06:07.090 align:middle line:84%
And you go through
it from there.

00:06:07.090 --> 00:06:10.060 align:middle line:84%
I have to say that my
mother was my first guru.

00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:12.650 align:middle line:84%
She put me on the
spiritual path.

00:06:12.650 --> 00:06:14.390 align:middle line:90%
She made things fun for me.

00:06:14.390 --> 00:06:18.661 align:middle line:84%
My mother made the practice of
Bhakti, a devotional life, fun

00:06:18.661 --> 00:06:19.360 align:middle line:90%
for me.

00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:22.530 align:middle line:10%
I think they had a very
happy childhood in Bhakti.

00:06:22.530 --> 00:06:26.950 align:middle line:10%
It was totally--
Bhakti was the thread

00:06:26.950 --> 00:06:29.260 align:middle line:10%
that ran through their life.

00:06:29.260 --> 00:06:33.330 align:middle line:84%
If you look throughout the
[INAUDIBLE], about the Vedas,

00:06:33.330 --> 00:06:37.100 align:middle line:84%
women are always glorified
as being more devotional,

00:06:37.100 --> 00:06:39.540 align:middle line:84%
thinking less with their head
and more with their heart

00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:42.510 align:middle line:84%
about their devotion,
more eager to just

00:06:42.510 --> 00:06:46.900 align:middle line:84%
throw aside rules and just do
what's right from the heart.

00:06:46.900 --> 00:06:50.060 align:middle line:84%
Devotion to my yoga
practice, devotion

00:06:50.060 --> 00:06:55.240 align:middle line:84%
to my teachers, devotion to
God, it's devotion to something

00:06:55.240 --> 00:06:57.310 align:middle line:90%
other than me, me, me, me, me.

00:06:57.310 --> 00:07:00.260 align:middle line:90%
Devotional service is selfless.

00:07:00.260 --> 00:07:05.540 align:middle line:84%
It's completely
just, I want make

00:07:05.540 --> 00:07:09.980 align:middle line:84%
this person happy and in
connection with the Lord.

00:07:09.980 --> 00:07:11.620 align:middle line:90%
You need to make that choice.

00:07:11.620 --> 00:07:13.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm choosing to be a giver.

00:07:13.530 --> 00:07:16.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm choosing to be kinder.

00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:18.420 align:middle line:90%
I'm choosing to be more loving.

00:07:18.420 --> 00:07:22.800 align:middle line:84%
I feel very, very grateful
that Bhakti yoga is becoming

00:07:22.800 --> 00:07:25.390 align:middle line:84%
something that is not
strange to Westerners,

00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:27.424 align:middle line:90%
but really is a healing path.

00:07:27.424 --> 00:07:31.870 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:31.870 --> 00:09:22.960 align:middle line:90%


00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:27.040 align:middle line:10%
As long as you're living
Bhakti, you give Bhakti.

00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:31.250 align:middle line:10%
So anybody who lives it
with some seriousness

00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:37.280 align:middle line:10%
and some sincerity,
then they automatically

00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:39.140 align:middle line:10%
give that to others.

00:09:39.140 --> 00:09:41.910 align:middle line:10%
And in that, and just
doing your path to Bhakti,

00:09:41.910 --> 00:09:43.070 align:middle line:10%
I see others see that.

00:09:43.070 --> 00:09:46.010 align:middle line:10%
And they want to join and do it.

00:09:46.010 --> 00:09:47.860 align:middle line:84%
Instead of saying,
you need to do this,

00:09:47.860 --> 00:09:50.490 align:middle line:84%
they see how happy
it makes all of us,

00:09:50.490 --> 00:09:52.580 align:middle line:90%
how healthy and conscious.

00:09:52.580 --> 00:09:54.450 align:middle line:84%
And people want to
be a part of that.

00:09:54.450 --> 00:09:56.765 align:middle line:84%
Just like a yoga practice
or a singing practice

00:09:56.765 --> 00:10:01.170 align:middle line:84%
or a instrument practice,
that faith and feeling

00:10:01.170 --> 00:10:04.840 align:middle line:84%
the unconditional
love from the source,

00:10:04.840 --> 00:10:08.650 align:middle line:84%
like any other practice, the
more we do it, the better at it

00:10:08.650 --> 00:10:09.712 align:middle line:90%
we get.

00:10:09.712 --> 00:10:11.750 align:middle line:84%
That's what the
practice is for.

00:10:11.750 --> 00:10:14.250 align:middle line:10%
That's what having a
daily [INAUDIBLE] is.

00:10:14.250 --> 00:10:17.070 align:middle line:10%
A daily conscious
practice is for me

00:10:17.070 --> 00:10:18.490 align:middle line:10%
to connect with my heart.

00:10:18.490 --> 00:10:22.860 align:middle line:84%
One major practice I
have is daily meditation.

00:10:22.860 --> 00:10:26.010 align:middle line:84%
And I meditate on
the names of God

00:10:26.010 --> 00:10:28.240 align:middle line:84%
in an ancient
practice called Japa.

00:10:28.240 --> 00:10:33.890 align:middle line:84%
Japa beads are used for prayer
and associating with God

00:10:33.890 --> 00:10:34.930 align:middle line:90%
through his holy names.

00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:37.930 align:middle line:10%
To experience Bhakti,
the most beautiful thing

00:10:37.930 --> 00:10:41.210 align:middle line:10%
is Japa, because
Japa is something

00:10:41.210 --> 00:10:45.660 align:middle line:10%
you can use your own body, your
own mind, and your own words,

00:10:45.660 --> 00:10:47.210 align:middle line:10%
and transform them.

00:10:47.210 --> 00:10:50.576 align:middle line:84%
You make that connection,
and that conscious connection,

00:10:50.576 --> 00:10:51.275 align:middle line:90%
your foundation.

00:10:51.275 --> 00:10:54.463 align:middle line:84%
And the whole rest of
the day is different.

00:10:54.463 --> 00:10:57.800 align:middle line:84%
And the whole rest of your
lifestyle is different.

00:10:57.800 --> 00:10:59.700 align:middle line:84%
And your whole connections
with other people

00:10:59.700 --> 00:11:01.420 align:middle line:84%
is different, which
makes them connect

00:11:01.420 --> 00:11:03.020 align:middle line:90%
with others differently.

00:11:03.020 --> 00:11:08.070 align:middle line:84%
So that foundation, as little
or as large as it may be,

00:11:08.070 --> 00:11:12.670 align:middle line:84%
can transform innumerable
different ways.

00:11:12.670 --> 00:11:21.680 align:middle line:84%
I start it like a
very regular practice

00:11:21.680 --> 00:11:25.540 align:middle line:84%
that I do every single
morning where I just

00:11:25.540 --> 00:11:27.750 align:middle line:90%
ask to be made an instrument.

00:11:27.750 --> 00:11:29.650 align:middle line:90%
I lift up my hands.

00:11:29.650 --> 00:11:34.540 align:middle line:84%
And I asked God to make an
instrument for his will.

00:11:34.540 --> 00:11:38.046 align:middle line:84%
RUKMINI WALKER: Only with
that mood of I have nothing,

00:11:38.046 --> 00:11:39.490 align:middle line:90%
but I have you.

00:11:39.490 --> 00:11:42.890 align:middle line:90%
That I'm yours, this is Bhakti.

00:11:42.890 --> 00:11:44.975 align:middle line:90%
I'm a pilgrim here.

00:11:44.975 --> 00:11:47.200 align:middle line:90%
I'm walking through this world.

00:11:47.200 --> 00:11:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And today or tomorrow
I'll be gone.

00:11:51.960 --> 00:11:54.797 align:middle line:90%
But that offering is eternal.

00:11:54.797 --> 00:11:59.288 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:59.288 --> 00:14:38.560 align:middle line:90%


00:14:38.560 --> 00:14:42.195 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:14:42.195 --> 00:14:51.990 align:middle line:90%


00:14:51.990 --> 00:14:59.110 align:middle line:84%
Kirtan allows you to open up
almost more than anything else.

00:14:59.110 --> 00:15:01.920 align:middle line:84%
It starts the process
of Bhakti almost quicker

00:15:01.920 --> 00:15:03.230 align:middle line:90%
than any other form.

00:15:03.230 --> 00:15:07.020 align:middle line:84%
Kirtan has become the
pathway in for so many

00:15:07.020 --> 00:15:08.270 align:middle line:90%
Western yoga practitioners.

00:15:08.270 --> 00:15:11.200 align:middle line:84%
I think it's so fast and
so efficient as a tool.

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:14.400 align:middle line:84%
For me, Bhakti just
means Kirtan and trying

00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:16.760 align:middle line:84%
to connect with the
holy name and the deeper

00:15:16.760 --> 00:15:17.700 align:middle line:90%
meaning of the name.

00:15:17.700 --> 00:15:21.120 align:middle line:90%
I feel like I go beyond myself.

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:22.360 align:middle line:90%
I will beyond the room.

00:15:22.360 --> 00:15:27.230 align:middle line:84%
Kirtan is such a specific,
different form of praise.

00:15:27.230 --> 00:15:32.420 align:middle line:84%
And it's-- it's just-- it
just lights you up, man.

00:15:32.420 --> 00:15:37.010 align:middle line:10%
Through sound we can reach
our true-- our true nature.

00:15:37.010 --> 00:15:39.800 align:middle line:10%
The mantra, vibration,
and you interact.

00:15:39.800 --> 00:15:41.790 align:middle line:10%
In other words, as you
sing it, then you're

00:15:41.790 --> 00:15:45.260 align:middle line:10%
gonna be pulled up into a
different energy that basically

00:15:45.260 --> 00:15:47.085 align:middle line:10%
has infinite possibility in it.

00:15:47.085 --> 00:15:48.760 align:middle line:84%
A lot of Americans
call it therapy.

00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:54.024 align:middle line:84%
But it's way beyond
therapy-- way beyond therapy.

00:15:54.024 --> 00:15:55.660 align:middle line:84%
There's living
imprints that happen

00:15:55.660 --> 00:16:01.390 align:middle line:84%
in the heart and the
mind that transform you.

00:16:01.390 --> 00:16:02.550 align:middle line:90%
I'd never experienced that.

00:16:02.550 --> 00:16:07.210 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to run for my life.

00:16:07.210 --> 00:16:11.750 align:middle line:84%
I was like, where's the
plane to leave my life?

00:16:11.750 --> 00:16:13.630 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know how I
was going to live.

00:16:13.630 --> 00:16:16.650 align:middle line:84%
It was devastation
on that level.

00:16:16.650 --> 00:16:24.780 align:middle line:84%
And I would just sing
[INAUDIBLE], you know?

00:16:24.780 --> 00:16:30.450 align:middle line:84%
And I would just keep
planting that seed.

00:16:30.450 --> 00:16:35.580 align:middle line:84%
And I use those words to replace
the other nasty words that were

00:16:35.580 --> 00:16:41.280 align:middle line:84%
going on in my head, you know,
words of blame or depression

00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:43.580 align:middle line:84%
or other feelings that I
didn't want to cultivate.

00:16:43.580 --> 00:16:45.110 align:middle line:10%
What we do is we
gather together

00:16:45.110 --> 00:16:46.330 align:middle line:10%
and we chant of
the names of God.

00:16:46.330 --> 00:16:49.320 align:middle line:10%
And in a sense, it's actually
calling out just like you'd

00:16:49.320 --> 00:16:50.530 align:middle line:10%
call out to a loved one.

00:16:50.530 --> 00:16:52.910 align:middle line:10%
You're saying their
name over and over.

00:16:52.910 --> 00:16:59.836 align:middle line:10%
If we offer our Kirtanas
to God, then God is pleased.

00:16:59.836 --> 00:17:06.060 align:middle line:10%
But it should be with
love from the heart,

00:17:06.060 --> 00:17:07.700 align:middle line:10%
not only from the tongue.

00:17:07.700 --> 00:17:09.540 align:middle line:10%
TULASI NADIA HARRISON:
Kirtan pierces your heart.

00:17:09.540 --> 00:17:12.829 align:middle line:10%
Kirtan really goes right
into the center and stays.

00:17:12.829 --> 00:17:15.210 align:middle line:10%
And every time you do
Kirtan it builds up.

00:17:15.210 --> 00:17:17.954 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually
the love bursts.

00:17:17.954 --> 00:17:20.560 align:middle line:84%
You end up giving
Kirtan to others.

00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:21.890 align:middle line:84%
So even when people
come who've never

00:17:21.890 --> 00:17:26.800 align:middle line:84%
sung before in their lives,
or say you know, I can't sing.

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:30.030 align:middle line:84%
You know, I have-- I'm
tone deaf and somebody told

00:17:30.030 --> 00:17:32.610 align:middle line:84%
me not to sing when I was in the
sixth grade chorus or whatever.

00:17:32.610 --> 00:17:34.390 align:middle line:90%
I say, this is different.

00:17:34.390 --> 00:17:36.140 align:middle line:90%
Everyone can sing God's name.

00:17:36.140 --> 00:17:38.771 align:middle line:84%
But even in ancient
times that, even

00:17:38.771 --> 00:17:42.600 align:middle line:84%
in the past few
hundred years in India,

00:17:42.600 --> 00:17:44.440 align:middle line:84%
ladies come together
and do Kirtan.

00:17:44.440 --> 00:17:47.160 align:middle line:84%
They have their ladies'
Kirtan and they come together.

00:17:47.160 --> 00:17:49.150 align:middle line:84%
It's said that women
relax by talking.

00:17:49.150 --> 00:17:52.070 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes men just
keep it all inside.

00:17:52.070 --> 00:17:55.670 align:middle line:84%
But when women come
together who are

00:17:55.670 --> 00:18:00.190 align:middle line:84%
longing for deep spirituality,
it can be very, very profound.

00:18:00.190 --> 00:18:04.290 align:middle line:10%
And Bhakti can be
the way and the goal

00:18:04.290 --> 00:18:06.790 align:middle line:10%
because you don't need
anything more than Bhakti.

00:18:06.790 --> 00:18:08.070 align:middle line:90%
It's not a way to something.

00:18:08.070 --> 00:18:10.150 align:middle line:90%
It can be a goal in itself.

00:18:10.150 --> 00:18:14.600 align:middle line:84%
And many devotees have said,
I don't want anything else.

00:18:14.600 --> 00:18:18.200 align:middle line:84%
I just want to sing about the
Supreme and be here forever.

00:18:18.200 --> 00:18:20.290 align:middle line:84%
And I think that from
that perspective,

00:18:20.290 --> 00:18:21.870 align:middle line:90%
this life is not bondage.

00:18:21.870 --> 00:18:23.580 align:middle line:90%
Its freedom.

00:18:23.580 --> 00:18:27.280 align:middle line:84%
This is moksha, to be
singing about the Supreme.

00:18:27.280 --> 00:18:28.990 align:middle line:90%
What more do you want?

00:18:28.990 --> 00:18:30.660 align:middle line:90%
You don't need to be in heaven.

00:18:30.660 --> 00:18:32.810 align:middle line:84%
You don't need to be in
any results exalted state.

00:18:32.810 --> 00:18:36.870 align:middle line:84%
When you hear about Bhakti
from the right source,

00:18:36.870 --> 00:18:40.220 align:middle line:84%
then you get an idea of
the greatness of Bhakti.

00:18:40.220 --> 00:18:43.810 align:middle line:84%
And that is amazing in that
it isn't something-- well,

00:18:43.810 --> 00:18:45.720 align:middle line:90%
I've heard that.

00:18:45.720 --> 00:18:47.050 align:middle line:90%
It's over.

00:18:47.050 --> 00:18:49.220 align:middle line:84%
The more you hear
about Bhakti, the more

00:18:49.220 --> 00:18:51.098 align:middle line:90%
you want to know about Bhakti.

